cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the optimization of sensing times in cognitive radio networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and signal processing, which are covered by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper deals with the interference caused by secondary users on primary channels, which is a topic related to control systems, covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with cognitive radio networks, which is a topic covered by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
